  <bioghist encodinganalog="545"> 
	 <head>Biographical Note</head> 
	 <p>Businessman and engineer, Nogales, Arizona. Began Miller's Assay Office
		in 1913; later Miller and Cox, 1921- 1924, later Hugo W. Miller Assay Office,
		1924-1958. </p> 
  </bioghist> 
  <arrangement> 
	 <head>Organization</head> 
	 <p>This collection is organized into two series: </p> 
	 <list> 
		<item>Series I: Personal and Financial Materials, 1902-1952</item> 
		<item>Series II: Ore and Assay Records, 1913-1958</item> 
	 </list> 
  </arrangement> 
  <scopecontent encodinganalog="520"> 
	 <head>Scope and Content Note</head> 
	 <p>Assay and ore records, and miscellaneous financial and administrative
		papers. Includes mill, smelter, and convertor reports for the Pride of the West
		Mining and Milling Company for 1902.</p> 
  </scopecontent> 
